  <titles>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Commodity Exchange Option Reform Amendments of 1988</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">A bill to amend the Commodity Exchange Act to improve federal regulation of commodities and instruments traded on, or otherwise capable of being traded on commodity exchanges governed by Commodity Futures Trading Commission rules; to better protect customers for such products; and to promote more efficient marketing through encouraging greater utilization of U.S. commodity exchanges.</title>
